### Case Management API — main flows (VS Code REST Client / JetBrains HTTP Client)
### Base URL — match your API (Docker demo: http://localhost:5202)
@host = http://localhost:5202

### Health (no auth)
GET {{host}}/api/health
Accept: application/json

###
### --- Register (creates user + personal org; skip if using seeded demo user) ---
# @name register
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "reviewer@example.local",
  "password": "ReviewPass1",
  "confirmPassword": "ReviewPass1",
  "firstName": "Review",
  "lastName": "User"
}

###
### --- Login (copy accessToken from response, or use variables below) ---
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.local",
  "password": "DemoPass1!"
}

###
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.$.accessToken}}

### Current user + organizations
GET {{host}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###
### Create case (uses active org from user profile)
# @name createCase
POST {{host}}/api/cases
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Demo case from HTTP file",
  "initialMessage": "First message on the case.",
  "priority": "medium",
  "requesterUserId": null
}

###
@caseId = {{createCase.response.body.$.id}}

### List cases (cursor API)
GET {{host}}/api/cases?limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###
### Case detail
GET {{host}}/api/cases/{{caseId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Accept: application/json

###
### Logout (invalidates refresh session; optional when testing with Bearer only)
POST {{host}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
